{{other ships|HMS Elk}}
{|{{Infobox ship begin}} {{Infobox ship image |Ship image= |Ship caption= }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship country= |Ship flag=[[File:Naval Ensign of the United Kingdom.svg|100x35px|Royal Navy Ensign]] |Ship name=HMS ''Elk'' |Ship namesake= |Ship ordered= |Ship builder=[[Chatham Dockyard]] |Ship laid down= |Ship launched=29 September 1847 |Ship acquired= |Ship commissioned= |Ship decommissioned=May 1893 |Ship homeport= |Ship motto= |Ship nickname= |Ship honours= |Ship fate=Sold in 1893 for breaking up |Ship notes= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Ship class=[[Acorn class brig|''Acorn''-class]] [[brig-sloop]]<ref name=RW>Winfield p. 128</ref> |Ship displacement=482 [[Builder's Old Measurement|BM]] |Ship length={{convert|105|ft|m|abbr=on}} |Ship beam={{convert|33|ft|m|abbr=on}} |Ship height= |Ship draught= |Ship depth= |Ship propulsion=Sail<ref name=RW>Winfield p. 128</ref> |Ship sail plan= |Ship speed= |Ship range= |Ship endurance= |Ship complement= |Ship armament=16 guns |Ship armour= |Ship notes= }} |} '''HMS ''Elk''''' was a 482-ton displacement, 16-gun [[Acorn class brig|''Acorn''-class]] [[brig-sloop]] of the [[Royal Navy]] launched on 29 September 1847 from the [[Chatham Dockyard]].<ref>Bastock, p.29.</ref>
She was sent to the [[East Indies Station]] and [[China Station]] and participated during the [[Second Opium War]] until being assigned to the [[Australia Station]] in 1859. She searched for [[HMS Sappho (1837)|HMS ''Sappho'']] with [[HMVS Victoria (1855)|HMVS ''Victoria'']] after ''Sappho'' disappeared in [[Bass Strait]] in February 1858. In 1860 she participated during the [[First Taranaki War]].<ref name="Bastock">Bastock, p.30.</ref> She left the Australia Station in March 1860 and upon arriving in England was [[Ship commissioning#Ship decommissioning|paid off]].
She was transferred to [[Her Majesty's Coastguard]] in 1863 and was renamed WV.13 and she was later renamed WV.28. She was sold in May 1893.<ref name="Bastock"/>
